The military will, which superseded the old testament in procinctu, could only be executed during actual service, and in this period only when the soldier was in camp, not when he was at home or on leave of absence. A will made after the soldier's dis- charge from service or during his absence from camp was governed

by the same rules as the will of a civilian (paganus). A military .

will, executed without the ordinary formalities, only remained valid during a year after discharge from service. Inst. 2, 11, 3.
